<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,289,530]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,289,314]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Poisson" box="[281,444,289,314]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Poisson, R. (1944) Contribution a la connaissance des especes africaines du genre Hebrus Curtis 1833 [Hemiptera Gymnocerata] (Missions de Ch. Alluaud et R. Jeannel en Afrique orientale). Revue Francaise d'Entomologie, Nouvelle Serie, 10 (3 - 4) [1943], 89 - 112." type="journal article" year="1944">Poisson (1944</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Poisson" box="[456,526,289,314]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Poisson, R. (1957 a) Heteropteres aquatiques. Faune de France, Vol. 61. Federation Francaise des Societes de Sciences Naturelles, Paris, 263 pp." type="book" year="1957" yearSuffix="a">1957a</bibRefCitation>
) diagnosed the new sugbenus 
<taxonomicName box="[871,996,289,314]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrusella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[871,996,289,314]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Hebrusella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on a single character: ‘Antennal segment IV completely divided into two segments (IVa and IVb) by true articulation’ (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Poisson" box="[1177,1332,325,350]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Poisson, R. (1944) Contribution a la connaissance des especes africaines du genre Hebrus Curtis 1833 [Hemiptera Gymnocerata] (Missions de Ch. Alluaud et R. Jeannel en Afrique orientale). Revue Francaise d'Entomologie, Nouvelle Serie, 10 (3 - 4) [1943], 89 - 112." type="journal article" year="1944">Poisson 1944</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1344,1411,325,350]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[178,1370,200,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[178,1399,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Hebrus atlas sp. nov.: 1 — micropterous male, paratype, Morocco: Ifrane env. (body length 1.82 mm); 2 — micropterous male, holotype, Morocco: Tazzeka NP (1.62 mm); 3 — micropterous female, paratype, Morocco: Tazzeka NP (1.76 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261265/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
C; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poisson" box="[151,317,361,386]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Poisson, R. (1957 a) Heteropteres aquatiques. Faune de France, Vol. 61. Federation Francaise des Societes de Sciences Naturelles, Paris, 263 pp." type="book" year="1957" yearSuffix="a">Poisson 1957a</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 129B; 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen" box="[454,627,361,386]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1982) The semiaquatic bugs (Hemiptera, Gerromorpha). Phylogeny, adaptations, biogeography and classification. Entomograph, Vol. 3. Scandiavian Science Press Ltd., Klampenborg, 455 pp." type="book" year="1982">Andersen 1982</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 114c; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[757,953,361,386]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (2006) Vodnye poluzhestkokrylye nasekomye (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) fauny Rossii i sopredelnykh stran. [Aquatic and semiaquatic (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) of the fauna of Russia and neighbouring countries]. Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, 296 pp. [in Russian, English abstract]" type="book" year="2006">Kanyukova 2006</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 372), whereas the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1329,1411,361,386]" class="Insecta" family="Hebridae" genus="Hebrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[1329,1411,361,386]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Hebrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="19" pageNumber="220" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has ‘segment IV incompletely divided by membranous ring, not fully articulated’ (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Poisson" box="[1167,1321,397,422]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Poisson, R. (1944) Contribution a la connaissance des especes africaines du genre Hebrus Curtis 1833 [Hemiptera Gymnocerata] (Missions de Ch. Alluaud et R. Jeannel en Afrique orientale). Revue Francaise d'Entomologie, Nouvelle Serie, 10 (3 - 4) [1943], 89 - 112." type="journal article" year="1944">Poisson 1944</bibRefCitation>
: 
<figureCitation box="[1332,1406,397,422]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 3" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1918,1941]" captionTargetBox="[178,1370,200,1859]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[178,1399,193,1876]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 3. Hebrus atlas sp. nov.: 1 — micropterous male, paratype, Morocco: Ifrane env. (body length 1.82 mm); 2 — micropterous male, holotype, Morocco: Tazzeka NP (1.62 mm); 3 — micropterous female, paratype, Morocco: Tazzeka NP (1.76 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/261265/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="220">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
D, 3D, 5D; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poisson" box="[249,416,433,458]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Poisson, R. (1957 a) Heteropteres aquatiques. Faune de France, Vol. 61. Federation Francaise des Societes de Sciences Naturelles, Paris, 263 pp." type="book" year="1957" yearSuffix="a">Poisson 1957a</bibRefCitation>
: Figs. 130B, 134C; 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen" box="[641,816,433,458]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Andersen, N. M. (1982) The semiaquatic bugs (Hemiptera, Gerromorpha). Phylogeny, adaptations, biogeography and classification. Entomograph, Vol. 3. Scandiavian Science Press Ltd., Klampenborg, 455 pp." type="book" year="1982">Andersen 1982</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 114b and Pl. C; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kanyukova" box="[1061,1258,433,458]" pageId="19" pageNumber="220" refString="Kanyukova, E. V. (2006) Vodnye poluzhestkokrylye nasekomye (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) fauny Rossii i sopredelnykh stran. [Aquatic and semiaquatic (Heteroptera: Nepomorpha, Gerromorpha) of the fauna of Russia and neighbouring countries]. Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, 296 pp. [in Russian, English abstract]" type="book" year="2006">Kanyukova 2006</bibRefCitation>
: Fig. 373). This character is difficult to observe and thus far, no other reliable character has been added to the diagnosis of the subgenus.
</paragraph>
